      <p><strong>Limits:</strong> {app.limits.join('; ')}.</p>
      <h2>Implementation playbook (30 days)</h2>
      <ol class="mt-5 list-decimal space-y-3 pl-6 text-slate-300">
        <li>Week 1: Inventory overlapping tools; assign owner; map consent sources.</li>
        <li>Week 2: Launch one revenue moment Recart should own — not five half-built flows.</li>
        <li>Week 3: Add capture, SMS, or proof handoffs with suppressions documented.</li>
        <li>Week 4: Compare Shopify orders vs platform attribution; adjust discount discipline.</li>
      </ol>
      <h2>Stack pairing patterns</h2>
      <p><strong>Lean stack:</strong> Privy capture → Sequenzy lifecycle → Postscript SMS for cart urgency → Shopify Analytics + weekly margin review.</p>
      <p><strong>Proof-heavy stack:</strong> Justuno quiz capture → Sequenzy lifecycle → Yotpo reviews in consideration flows → Marsello loyalty on repeat.</p>
      <p><strong>Data-max stack:</strong> Klaviyo lifecycle + SMS when team lives in segments daily — Recart only if it fills a gap Klaviyo does not.</p>
      <h2>When to choose Recart vs Sequenzy lifecycle layer</h2>
      <p>Choose Sequenzy when lifecycle strategy, pay-per-email economics, and agent-first playbooks are the bottleneck. Choose Recart when sms & messenger recovery is the binding constraint and you already have lifecycle ownership elsewhere — or when Recart truly runs welcome through winback with collision controls.</p>
        <h2>Seven-layer stack map for Recart</h2>
        <h3>Capture layer: Privy, Justuno</h3>
        <p>Popups, quizzes, exit intent feeding qualified subscribers with source tags for welcome branching. In Recart, assign an owner and first-month deliverable before install. Test handoff into Sequenzy lifecycle with suppressions when popup offer already delivered.</p>
        <p>Failure mode: capture layer runs independently — shopper receives popup discount, cart email discount, and SMS discount same day. Fix with collision calendar, not more software.</p>
        <p>Operator test: can you name the single metric that proves capture layer improved margin last month? If not, pause new installs until measurement exists.</p>
        <h3>Lifecycle layer: Sequenzy</h3>
        <p>Welcome through winback, replenishment, education — agent-first with pay-per-email economics. In Recart, assign an owner and first-month deliverable before install. Test handoff into Sequenzy lifecycle with suppressions when popup offer already delivered.</p>
        <p>Failure mode: lifecycle layer runs independently — shopper receives popup discount, cart email discount, and SMS discount same day. Fix with collision calendar, not more software.</p>
        <p>Operator test: can you name the single metric that proves lifecycle layer improved margin last month? If not, pause new installs until measurement exists.</p>
        <h3>SMS urgency: Postscript, SMSBump</h3>
        <p>Cart recovery and drop alerts after email silence; TCPA and quiet hours non-negotiable. In Recart, assign an owner and first-month deliverable before install. Test handoff into Sequenzy lifecycle with suppressions when popup offer already delivered.</p>
        <p>Failure mode: sms urgency runs independently — shopper receives popup discount, cart email discount, and SMS discount same day. Fix with collision calendar, not more software.</p>
        <p>Operator test: can you name the single metric that proves sms urgency improved margin last month? If not, pause new installs until measurement exists.</p>
        <h3>Proof layer: Yotpo</h3>
